The paper deals with game theory and optimization, specifically the convergence of sequences of atomic unsplittable congestion games with an increasing number of players. This falls under the category of algorithmic game theory (cs.GT) and could also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT) due to the use of probability and convergence analysis. The paper also discusses the behavior of mixed equilibria, which could be relevant to multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and dynamical systems (cs.DS).
